and he's calling me to ask me
if he can bring his new girlfriend to it.

765
00:32:11,223 --> 00:32:13,225
[groans] That bitch.

766
00:32:13,308 --> 00:32:16,019
No, she's actually a really nice person.

767
00:32:16,103 --> 00:32:19,940
- Oh, she is? Well, that's great.
- I hate her 50-year-old guts so much.

768
00:32:20,023 --> 00:32:22,693
I'll be honest, I don't know
what you're looking for with this story.

769
00:32:22,776 --> 00:32:24,987
- [chuckles] I know it's confusing.
- Yeah. [chuckles]

770
00:32:25,070 --> 00:32:26,655
Well, here's the thing.

771
00:32:26,738 --> 00:32:31,118
When I left him,
I thought that I was gonna be the winner

772
00:32:31,201 --> 00:32:32,452
- of the divorce.
- Sure.

773
00:32:32,536 --> 00:32:37,040
But now he's parading her all around,
and I'm still single.

774
00:32:37,124 --> 00:32:39,710
- And so I, of course, cannot…
- And that hurts.

775
00:32:40,544 --> 00:32:41,795
…show my face there.

776
00:32:41,879 --> 00:32:43,630
- Oh, you're not gonna go.
- No.

777
00:32:44,423 --> 00:32:46,216
- That sucks.
- Yeah.

778
00:32:46,300 --> 00:32:49,386
- But why'd you leave him?
- He was just such a child.

779
00:32:49,469 --> 00:32:51,346
He had no aspirations.

780
00:32:51,430 --> 00:32:55,893
He didn't have many friends,
just one weird friend really,

781
00:32:55,976 --> 00:32:59,688
who just was, "Yes, yes, yes"
to everything he said.

782
00:32:59,771 --> 00:33:01,106
He was sort of a suck-up.

783
00:33:01,190 --> 00:33:05,944
And he was always telling these boring,
boring stories about his glory days.

784
00:33:06,028 --> 00:33:07,613
Ah, he doesn't sound so bad.

785
00:33:07,696 --> 00:33:09,364
The truth is,

786
00:33:09,448 --> 00:33:14,119
I would've put up with all that
if he'd ever just shown up for me.

787
00:33:17,539 --> 00:33:18,707
Hey!

788
00:33:18,790 --> 00:33:21,293
You two gonna hog the court
and gab all night

789
00:33:21,376 --> 00:33:23,045
or you looking to run some pickle?

790
00:33:23,128 --> 00:33:24,671
We'll run some pickle!

791
00:33:24,755 --> 00:33:26,423
- Is that okay with you?
- Yeah.

792
00:33:27,049 --> 00:33:28,091
- We'll be partners.
- Yep.

793
00:33:28,175 --> 00:33:31,136
- Let's do it.
- What are they though?

794
00:33:31,220 --> 00:33:32,596
[grunts]

795
00:33:34,139 --> 00:33:35,140
[grunts]

796
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:37,809
[grunts]

797
00:33:38,769 --> 00:33:39,770
[grunts]

798
00:33:40,771 --> 00:33:43,607
- [grunts] Uh-huh, uh-huh.
- Ooh! Yes! Ooh!

799
00:33:43,690 --> 00:33:45,859
I can't with these two.
I honestly can't do another second.

800
00:33:45,943 --> 00:33:47,861
- Listen. Okay, they're grunters.
- What?

801
00:33:47,945 --> 00:33:50,197
- You think?
- I've played people like this before,

802
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:53,784
and the only way to beat them
is to out-grunt them.

803
00:33:53,867 --> 00:33:56,411
Or we could beat them
by being better players, which we are.

804
00:33:56,495 --> 00:33:58,789
No, that'll never work.
We have to do it my way.

805
00:33:58,872 --> 00:34:00,582
Grunt with me, Dusty.

806
00:34:00,666 --> 00:34:04,628
And the more erotic, the better.

807
00:34:04,711 --> 00:34:08,047
You can strategize all you want,
but it's not gonna help.

808
00:34:08,130 --> 00:34:10,967
Yeah, everyone has a plan
until they get punched in the mouth.

809
00:34:11,051 --> 00:34:12,219
- Let's just play.
- [player 1] Okay.

810
00:34:12,302 --> 00:34:14,304
- [player 2] All right. Let's play.
- [player 1] Okay.

811
00:34:14,388 --> 00:34:16,764
["Get Up Offa That Thing" playing]

812
00:34:16,849 --> 00:34:17,850
Whatever it takes, right?

813
00:34:17,933 --> 00:34:19,059
Yeah.

814
00:34:22,187 --> 00:34:23,981
- [grunts weakly]
- Oh, God.

815
00:34:24,063 --> 00:34:25,190
[grunts]

816
00:34:25,274 --> 00:34:26,733
[grunts]

817
00:34:26,817 --> 00:34:28,110
[grunts]

818
00:34:29,069 --> 00:34:30,445
Okay.

819
00:34:31,697 --> 00:34:32,697
[grunts]

820
00:34:33,739 --> 00:34:35,074
[grunts]

821
00:34:36,034 --> 00:34:37,244
[grunts]

822
00:34:38,120 --> 00:34:41,540
[all grunting]

823
00:34:41,623 --> 00:34:42,833
[grunts intensely]

824
00:34:42,916 --> 00:34:46,128
[grunting]

825
00:34:46,210 --> 00:34:47,670
Ay, papi!

826
00:34:48,547 --> 00:34:49,755
