I'm really sorry and embarrassed
about what I said the other night.

1673
01:14:37,561 --> 01:14:40,564
I do wanna be friends with you. [chuckles]

1674
01:14:40,647 --> 01:14:42,441
I like you a lot.

1675
01:14:42,524 --> 01:14:43,692
Me too.

1676
01:14:43,775 --> 01:14:46,445
Truth is I don't have
very many good friends anymore.

1677
01:14:47,988 --> 01:14:50,407
And when I was listing 'em
and I said Gail,

1678
01:14:51,200 --> 01:14:54,203
actually it wasn't a different Gail.
It was your Gail.

1679
01:14:54,286 --> 01:14:55,204
I know.

1680
01:14:55,287 --> 01:14:57,331
And I don't even know
if Gail likes me very much.

1681
01:14:57,414 --> 01:14:59,416
- She doesn't.
- [chuckles]

1682
01:15:00,250 --> 01:15:01,960
But I'm in the same boat.

1683
01:15:02,044 --> 01:15:07,591
I mean, Mitch got most of our friends
in the divorce.

1684
01:15:08,133 --> 01:15:10,052
- Traitors.
- [chuckles]

1685
01:15:10,135 --> 01:15:13,722
That's why it meant so much to me
when you showed up the other night.

1686
01:15:17,100 --> 01:15:18,101
We're good.

1687
01:15:18,185 --> 01:15:19,186
- Yeah?
- We're good!

1688
01:15:19,269 --> 01:15:20,270
- We're buds?
- Yeah.

1689
01:15:20,354 --> 01:15:21,355
- For sure?
- Yeah.

1690
01:15:21,438 --> 01:15:22,439
All right, bud.

1691
01:15:22,523 --> 01:15:23,857
[both chuckle]

1692
01:15:25,442 --> 01:15:28,278
I mean, speaking of showing up
for each other,

1693
01:15:28,946 --> 01:15:31,114
there's something
I could use your help with.

1694
01:15:31,698 --> 01:15:32,824
What are you thinking?

1695
01:15:36,703 --> 01:15:38,205
We lost a few times, yeah.

1696
01:15:38,288 --> 01:15:39,414
Any sign of Dusty?

1697
01:15:39,498 --> 01:15:41,458
- Haven't seen him yet. No.
- Mm-mmm. No.

1698
01:15:41,542 --> 01:15:45,087
Hey, Chuck! It's Dusty. He just arrived.

1699
01:15:45,170 --> 01:15:47,673
["King Talk" playing]

1700
01:16:29,256 --> 01:16:30,257
[music ends]

1701
01:16:30,340 --> 01:16:32,134
Can I have everyone's attention please?

1702
01:16:32,801 --> 01:16:34,761
There's something important I need to say.

1703
01:16:34,845 --> 01:16:36,388
Dusty, maybe you and I should talk first.

1704
01:16:36,471 --> 01:16:38,390
No, Chuck. I have the floor.

1705
01:16:38,473 --> 01:16:39,516
Okay.

1706
01:16:39,600 --> 01:16:40,601
Okay.

1707
01:16:41,685 --> 01:16:45,397
I wrote something out.
And you guys are gonna hear me out.

1708
01:16:45,480 --> 01:16:46,982
What is bravery?

1709
01:16:48,358 --> 01:16:49,401
Is it camping?

1710
01:16:50,527 --> 01:16:52,946
Sorry, I can't read my own handwriting.
It's a little bit smudged.

1711
01:16:53,030 --> 01:16:54,990
It can't be camping, uh…

1712
01:16:55,073 --> 01:16:58,493
[stammers] What is bravery? Um… Is it--

1713
01:16:58,577 --> 01:16:59,661
How long is this?

1714
01:16:59,745 --> 01:17:01,079
Not long. It's pretty short.

1715
01:17:06,001 --> 01:17:07,461
Actually, it's over.

1716
01:17:12,007 --> 01:17:14,009
[inhales deeply] For a long time, Dad,

1717
01:17:14,092 --> 01:17:16,803
I have been pretending
to be somebody I'm not,

1718
01:17:17,763 --> 01:17:18,931
but that's over now.

1719
01:17:19,806 --> 01:17:23,060
This is me, Dad. [chuckles]
For better or for worse.

1720
01:17:23,143 --> 01:17:27,147
And you don't respect me.
And you never have.

1721
01:17:27,231 --> 01:17:29,399
So I'm not gonna play for you.

1722
01:17:29,483 --> 01:17:33,987
I'm gonna enter the duel,
but not for the tennis side.

1723
01:17:35,030 --> 01:17:37,866
Today, I'm playing for the pickleballers.

1724
01:17:37,950 --> 01:17:39,159
- [gasps]
- Yes!

1725
01:17:39,243 --> 01:17:42,037
- I just am. You left me no choice, Dad.
- [laughing]

1726
01:17:42,120 --> 01:17:44,122
- [Judy] Yes!
- Wait, wait, wait. Whoa, whoa.

1727
01:17:44,206 --> 01:17:46,124
We can talk about this.
I mean, I'm ready to rock--

1728
01:17:46,208 --> 01:17:47,501
Nah, Skip, you're terrible.
I'm gonna do it.

1729
01:17:47,584 --> 01:17:49,336
- I'm gonna do it for sure.
- It's gonna be Dusty.

1730
01:17:49,419 --> 01:17:51,964
[pickleballers chanting]
Dusty! Dusty! Dusty!

1731
01:17:52,047 --> 01:17:53,882
Yeah, Dad. Hammer's back.

1732
01:17:55,300 --> 01:17:57,469
Okay. Settle down everyone.

1733
01:17:58,303 --> 01:18:01,807
Can't believe I'm saying this,
but my son's right.

1734
01:18:01,890 --> 01:18:03,016
[chuckles]

1735
01:18:03,100 --> 01:18:04,309
I never had faith in him.

1736
01:18:04,393 --> 01:18:06,645
He was a backup option,

1737
01:18:06,728 --> 01:18:10,566
which is why I was working the phones,
pulling strings,

1738
01:18:10,649 --> 01:18:13,151
to get a real player for the match today.

1739
01:18:13,902 --> 01:18:18,198
Three-time Wimbledon finalist,
2003 US Open champion.

1740
01:18:18,282 --> 01:18:21,702
Ladies and gentlemen, please give
a big welcome to Mr. Andy Roddick!

1741
01:18:22,327 --> 01:18:24,121
- What?
- [exclaiming, clamoring]

1742
01:18:24,204 --> 01:18:25,455
Oh.

1743
01:18:26,707 --> 01:18:29,334
I cannot tell you how grateful I am
that you went first.

1744
01:18:29,418 --> 01:18:32,296
I would've looked like a real asshole
replacing my son like that,

1745
01:18:32,379 --> 01:18:34,214
but it all just worked out perfect.

1746
01:18:34,298 --> 01:18:36,842
Perfect. Yeah, it's just perfect.
Just how I drew it up.

1747
01:18:36,925 --> 01:18:39,011
- Okay, okay. Back off him, folks.
- [Kris laughing]

1748
01:18:39,094 --> 01:18:42,014
The match will be played at high noon
as written in the charter.

1749
01:18:42,097 --> 01:18:44,224
I'm ready to play now if you want.
I'm gonna kill him.

1750
01:18:44,308 --> 01:18:47,477
[chuckles] I'm sure you are, kiddo,
but let's do this by the book.

1751
01:18:47,561 --> 01:18:51,148
I just hope no one freaks out so bad
that they bail all together.

1752
01:18:53,233 --> 01:18:54,443
- Dusty, it's okay.
- No.

1753
01:18:54,526 --> 01:18:55,527
[suspenseful music playing]

1754
01:18:55,611 --> 01:18:58,864
Oh, no! Oh, no!

1755
01:18:58,947 --> 01:19:00,949
- Maybe you could beat him.
- [Dusty] At tennis?

1756
01:19:01,033 --> 01:19:03,702
I can't beat Andy Roddick.
It's Andy Roddick!

1757
01:19:03,785 --> 01:19:06,955
He is so much better than me, Candace!

1758
01:19:07,039 --> 01:19:09,625
And he always has been, okay?

1759
01:19:09,708 --> 01:19:12,294
Dusty, your dad's using
this charter loophole

1760
01:19:12,377 --> 01:19:14,254
against the pickleball players, right?

1761
01:19:14,338 --> 01:19:17,090
Yeah. Maybe there's something
in there that can help us.

1762
01:19:17,174 --> 01:19:18,467
No, it's not gonna work.

1763
01:19:18,550 --> 01:19:20,969
It's worth a look.
I mean, I always keep a copy on me.

1764
01:19:21,053 --> 01:19:22,721
Nice. Here. I'll do it.

1765
01:19:22,804 --> 01:19:25,474
You always keep a copy
of the club charter in your fanny pack?

1766
01:19:25,557 --> 01:19:27,184
You never know when you're gonna need it.

1767
01:19:27,267 --> 01:19:29,436
What's one other time
that you've needed it?

1768
01:19:29,520 --> 01:19:30,521
I need some air.

1769
01:19:31,230 --> 01:19:33,232
[chattering]

1770
01:19:41,240 --> 01:19:42,241
[music ends]

1771
01:19:46,870 --> 01:19:48,372
[sighs]

1772
01:19:48,455 --> 01:19:50,082
Your game's in five.

1773
01:19:53,418 --> 01:19:54,419
[sighs]

1774
01:19:55,754 --> 01:19:57,589
You sure you wanna go through with this?

1775
01:19:59,925 --> 01:20:01,343
How'd you know I was in here?

1776
01:20:01,885 --> 01:20:03,887
You're always in here before a match.

1777
01:20:04,638 --> 01:20:05,806
Sometimes during.

1778
01:20:06,390 --> 01:20:07,558
[chuckles] Right.

1779
01:20:10,435 --> 01:20:11,854
Not too late to back out.

1780
01:20:15,357 --> 01:20:17,359
[suspenseful music playing]

1781
01:20:32,249 --> 01:20:34,042
Just in time for the coin toss.

1782
01:20:34,126 --> 01:20:35,210
We'll let you call it.

1783
01:20:35,294 --> 01:20:37,296
Might be the only thing
you have a chance of winning today.

1784
01:20:37,379 --> 01:20:39,131
- [all laugh]
- Very funny, Andy.

1785
01:20:39,214 --> 01:20:40,883
What'll it be, Son? Heads or tails?

1786
01:20:40,966 --> 01:20:42,217
Uh, let's go with tails.

1787
01:20:44,219 --> 01:20:45,596
Tails it is.

1788
01:20:46,263 --> 01:20:47,556
Would you like to serve or receive?

1789
01:20:47,639 --> 01:20:49,057
[Candace] Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1790
01:20:49,141 --> 01:20:50,267
Hey.

1791
01:20:52,102 --> 01:20:54,438
- What? Do you think? Really?
- Just… Yeah.

1792
01:20:55,022 --> 01:20:57,024
Okay. I'd like to choose the court.

1793
01:20:57,107 --> 01:20:59,693
- The court? Ooh. That should help.
- [laughs]

1794
01:20:59,776 --> 01:21:00,777
[Dusty] It might. [chuckles]

1795
01:21:00,861 --> 01:21:02,738
I choose court 16.

1796
01:21:02,821 --> 01:21:03,947
- What?
- Yeah.

1797
01:21:04,031 --> 01:21:05,657
No. This is a tennis club.

1798
01:21:05,741 --> 01:21:07,743
It's a tennis match.
Play it on a tennis court.

1799
01:21:07,826 --> 01:21:10,829
No, no, no.
It says it right here in the charter.

1800
01:21:10,913 --> 01:21:16,668
"Winner of the toss may select any court
on club grounds to play the match."

1801
01:21:16,752 --> 01:21:17,628
- Yes.
- Right here.

1802
01:21:17,711 --> 01:21:20,172
What's the big deal? Why is everyone
freaking out about court 16?

1803
01:21:20,255 --> 01:21:22,508
It's pickleball, bitch.

1804
01:21:22,591 --> 01:21:23,592
[audience cheering]

1805
01:21:23,675 --> 01:21:26,929
[dramatic music playing]

1806
01:21:31,600 --> 01:21:33,560
[chattering]

1807
01:21:40,150 --> 01:21:42,444
He's got this. He has got this.

1808
01:21:42,528 --> 01:21:43,529
[clears throat]

1809
01:21:43,612 --> 01:21:44,613
[chuckles]

1810
01:21:47,574 --> 01:21:50,160
Wait. Are you John McEnroe?

1811
01:21:50,244 --> 01:21:52,412
What gave me away? My face and body?

1812
01:21:52,496 --> 01:21:53,997
What are you doing here?

1813
01:21:54,081 --> 01:21:57,334
I heard there was a big game.
I love the action.

1814
01:22:02,673 --> 01:22:06,927
Gentlemen, game is to 11. Win by two.

1815
01:22:07,010 --> 01:22:08,345
Any questions about the rules?

1816
01:22:08,428 --> 01:22:10,472
No, let's just get this over with. [sighs]

1817
01:22:10,556 --> 01:22:13,600
[audience cheering]

1818
01:22:22,317 --> 01:22:23,318
[mouthing] Asshole.

1819
01:22:28,740 --> 01:22:30,158
[eagle calls]

1820
01:22:30,742 --> 01:22:33,245
[tense music playing]

1821
01:22:33,871 --> 01:22:34,872
[sighs]

1822
01:22:43,714 --> 01:22:44,882
[sighs]

1823
01:22:52,973 --> 01:22:55,809
[upbeat rock music playing]

1824
01:22:55,893 --> 01:22:57,227
- Yes. Yes!
- [Gail] Whoo!

1825
01:22:57,311 --> 01:22:58,437
[laughs]

1826
01:22:58,937 --> 01:23:00,147
[groans]

1827
01:23:00,230 --> 01:23:01,231
Trust me.

1828
01:23:04,193 --> 01:23:05,569
- Come on, Andy!
- Go, Andy!

1829
01:23:05,652 --> 01:23:07,070
Andy! Let's go!

1830
01:23:09,907 --> 01:23:10,908
[groans]

1831
01:23:10,991 --> 01:23:12,534
[audience groans]

1832
01:23:12,618 --> 01:23:13,785
- Yes!
- Yeah.

1833
01:23:14,286 --> 01:23:17,164
Oh, I get it now.
It's like tennis but easy.

1834
01:23:17,247 --> 01:23:18,332
[chuckles]

1835
01:23:19,541 --> 01:23:21,376
He hits it so hard. [pants]

1836
01:23:22,377 --> 01:23:23,837
[grunts]

1837
01:23:25,464 --> 01:23:26,465
[groans]

1838
01:23:26,548 --> 01:23:28,509
[audience cheering]

1839
01:23:33,305 --> 01:23:35,807
[McEnroe] There's that
trademark Roddick speed.

1840
01:23:35,891 --> 01:23:39,728
Dusty doesn't have any room to breathe.
This could get out of hand quickly.

1841
01:23:39,811 --> 01:23:41,813
Who are you talking to?

1842
01:23:41,897 --> 01:23:42,940
The fans.

1843
01:23:43,941 --> 01:23:46,610
[audience exclaiming, chattering]

1844
01:23:46,693 --> 01:23:48,153
Let's watch this next point

1845
01:23:48,237 --> 01:23:51,323
and see how Dusty responds
to this latest flurry from Andy.

1846
01:23:51,406 --> 01:23:53,951
Yeah, we're planning on it. Thank you.

1847
01:23:54,034 --> 01:23:55,452
Good. That's good to hear.

1848
01:23:56,870 --> 01:23:57,871
[groans]

1849
01:23:58,539 --> 01:24:00,332
- [grunts]
- [groans]

1850
01:24:00,415 --> 01:24:01,500
[audience groans]

1851
01:24:01,583 --> 01:24:02,876
[laughs]

1852
01:24:04,628 --> 01:24:06,630
- [grunts]
- [groans]

1853
01:24:06,713 --> 01:24:07,714
[audience cheers]

1854
01:24:07,798 --> 01:24:10,133
Who do you think you are? I am!

1855
01:24:10,634 --> 01:24:11,635
[groans]

1856
01:24:14,263 --> 01:24:15,264
Come on!

1857
01:24:15,347 --> 01:24:17,266
- [audience cheering]
- [spectator] Come on, Andy!

1858
01:24:17,349 --> 01:24:21,770
[McEnroe] It's looking like the lights
are just too bright for Boyd out there.

1859
01:24:21,854 --> 01:24:23,272
Maybe he can come back.

1860
01:24:23,355 --> 01:24:25,065
Not likely, but I hope so.

1861
01:24:25,148 --> 01:24:26,942
Not only for the sake of the crowd…

1862
01:24:27,025 --> 01:24:28,986
You need some rest or, like, oxygen?

1863
01:24:29,069 --> 01:24:31,154
[McEnroe] …but for Dusty as an individual.

1864
01:24:31,238 --> 01:24:34,950
Boldly trying to reclaim
his identity in his mid-40s,

1865
01:24:35,033 --> 01:24:38,120
his father's club hanging in the balance.

1866
01:24:38,203 --> 01:24:40,455
How do you have so many details?

1867
01:24:40,539 --> 01:24:44,168
Ooh. Where did you get that hotdog?
Do they sell those here?

1868
01:24:44,251 --> 01:24:46,128
Nope. Brought it from home.

1869
01:24:46,795 --> 01:24:50,257
[breathing heavily]

1870
01:24:50,340 --> 01:24:53,343
[muffled jeering]

1871
01:25:01,185 --> 01:25:02,186
[muffled] Get up!

1872
01:25:06,982 --> 01:25:08,859
[Skip, muffled] Use the court.

1873
01:25:09,943 --> 01:25:11,111
[normal] What?

1874
01:25:11,195 --> 01:25:13,155
[muffled] Use the court.

1875
01:25:14,364 --> 01:25:16,283
[normal] What are you saying?

1876
01:25:16,366 --> 01:25:17,409
The messed up court!

1877
01:25:17,492 --> 01:25:19,578
Use it to your advantage,
you stupid asshole.

1878
01:25:19,661 --> 01:25:21,371
[upbeat music playing]

1879
01:25:21,455 --> 01:25:23,790
[chuckling]

1880
01:25:26,043 --> 01:25:28,253
[Skip] The southeast fence is too close.

1881
01:25:35,844 --> 01:25:37,387
[audience gasping]

1882
01:25:37,971 --> 01:25:39,264
- Ooh.
- Oh!

1883
01:25:39,348 --> 01:25:40,766
Fence is too close.

1884
01:25:43,685 --> 01:25:46,355
[audience applauding, cheering]

1885
01:25:46,438 --> 01:25:47,731
Yeah!

1886
01:25:50,651 --> 01:25:53,278
Get it together, Andy! Walk it off!

1887
01:25:53,362 --> 01:25:56,532
[Skip] The baseline corner
is warped and cracked.

1888
01:26:00,577 --> 01:26:01,703
[audience groans]

1889
01:26:01,787 --> 01:26:03,497
Into the crack! [clears throat]

1890
01:26:04,122 --> 01:26:05,415
[grunts]

1891
01:26:05,499 --> 01:26:06,875
Chuck, your courts suck.

1892
01:26:09,127 --> 01:26:10,546
[Kris] Come on, Andy!

1893
01:26:10,629 --> 01:26:12,506
- Go, Andy!
- Andy! Let's go!

1894
01:26:13,090 --> 01:26:14,508
[Skip] And all the pickleballers know

1895
01:26:14,591 --> 01:26:17,970
that the leaky fountain
leaves a very slippery puddle

1896
01:26:18,053 --> 01:26:19,388
near the net post.

1897
01:26:26,728 --> 01:26:28,063
[grunts]

1898
01:26:28,689 --> 01:26:29,773
[audience gasps]

1899
01:26:29,857 --> 01:26:31,608
- [exclaims]
- [groans]

1900
01:26:32,609 --> 01:26:34,069
[groans]

1901
01:26:34,152 --> 01:26:35,153
You okay?

1902
01:26:35,237 --> 01:26:36,530
[audience applauding]

1903
01:26:36,613 --> 01:26:37,614
It's slippery right there.

1904
01:26:38,615 --> 01:26:40,033
Dad, we've gotta fix that.

1905
01:26:41,869 --> 01:26:42,870
What a good sport.

1906
01:26:43,620 --> 01:26:46,540
That run has completely
changed the momentum.

1907
01:26:46,623 --> 01:26:49,209
It's become the Dusty show on court 16,

1908
01:26:49,293 --> 01:26:53,630
and you can feel the tension from Gary,
Chuck and all the other tennis folk.

1909
01:26:53,714 --> 01:26:56,008
Are you reading off of something?

1910
01:26:56,091 --> 01:26:58,218
I'm just reading the expressions
of the crowd

1911
01:26:58,302 --> 01:26:59,928
and the body language of the players.

1912
01:27:00,012 --> 01:27:04,266
Now Dusty's got a glimmer of hope.
Sometimes that's all you need.

1913
01:27:04,349 --> 01:27:07,019
[upbeat music playing]

1914
01:27:12,482 --> 01:27:13,567
[audience cheering]

1915
01:27:18,655 --> 01:27:19,907
[audience groans]

1916
01:27:22,910 --> 01:27:24,328
- Yeah!
- [audience cheering]

1917
01:27:25,204 --> 01:27:26,205
Damn it!

1918
01:27:30,751 --> 01:27:31,752
Boom!

1919
01:27:31,835 --> 01:27:33,795
[audience cheering]

1920
01:27:33,879 --> 01:27:36,423
Hey, uh, Andy. You leave the fridge open?

1921
01:27:37,716 --> 01:27:39,676
Hey, chef, grab me a snack!

1922
01:27:39,760 --> 01:27:41,428
Do the dishes
while you're in there, bitch!

1923
01:27:41,512 --> 01:27:43,013
[Judy] Where's the butter knife?

1924
01:27:43,096 --> 01:27:45,349
Sorry, just a little inside joke
I have with my friends.

1925
01:27:45,432 --> 01:27:47,893
Your friends? You mean
those 70-year-old women you came with?

1926
01:27:47,976 --> 01:27:49,686
Yeah, them.

1927
01:27:49,770 --> 01:27:52,147
You're in the kitchen though, Andy.
It's my point.

1928
01:27:52,231 --> 01:27:53,857
[audience cheering]

1929
01:27:55,108 --> 01:27:56,318
[McEnroe] It's match point.

1930
01:27:56,401 --> 01:27:58,612
Dusty's got an opportunity
to close him out,

1931
01:27:58,695 --> 01:28:00,781
but Roddick's been in tight spots before

1932
01:28:00,864 --> 01:28:02,533
and he ain't going down without a fight.

1933
01:28:03,659 --> 01:28:05,661
[tense music playing]

1934
01:28:06,870 --> 01:28:10,040
[breathes heavily]

1935
01:28:10,123 --> 01:28:11,375
[sighs]

1936
01:28:27,140 --> 01:28:28,141
[grunts]

1937
01:28:35,899 --> 01:28:38,777
Dusty's completely transformed his style.

1938
01:28:38,861 --> 01:28:42,030
Oh, it's almost as if he realized
it's never too late to change.

1939
01:28:42,114 --> 01:28:43,115
Hit the ball.

1940
01:28:43,198 --> 01:28:45,200
Letting softness be his strength.

1941
01:28:45,284 --> 01:28:49,371
Finally releasing an old idea of himself
that no longer serves him.

1942
01:28:49,454 --> 01:28:51,206
Well said, John McEnroe.

1943
01:28:51,290 --> 01:28:53,333
All right. Fine. We'll do it your way.

1944
01:28:53,417 --> 01:28:55,294
[McEnroe] Yeah, I expected this.

1945
01:28:55,377 --> 01:28:57,588
Roddick is good at in-game adjustments.

1946
01:28:57,671 --> 01:28:59,840
He's decided to match Dusty's style.

1947
01:28:59,923 --> 01:29:02,426
I think we got ourselves
an old-fashioned dink off.

1948
01:29:03,051 --> 01:29:04,469
Hit it, Hammer. Hit the ball.

1949
01:29:08,891 --> 01:29:11,393
- What the hell are they doing?
- They're dinking.

1950
01:29:17,566 --> 01:29:18,775
What happens now?

1951
01:29:18,859 --> 01:29:20,027
[Kris] Now we wait.

1952
01:29:21,278 --> 01:29:22,696
- Seriously?
- Mm-hmm.

1953
01:29:22,779 --> 01:29:24,406
[Chuck] That's what this game is?

1954
01:29:24,489 --> 01:29:25,824
[Gary] Pretty much, yeah.

1955
01:29:25,908 --> 01:29:28,493
They dink till someone pops it up
too high and gets crushed.

1956
01:29:28,577 --> 01:29:29,912
This is really stupid.

1957
01:29:34,541 --> 01:29:36,126
[music continues]

1958
01:29:37,961 --> 01:29:40,923
[McEnroe] Two heavyweights
in a high-stakes tickle fight.

1959
01:29:41,006 --> 01:29:42,799
Who will be the first to giggle?

1960
01:29:43,383 --> 01:29:44,426
[grunts]

1961
01:29:49,723 --> 01:29:50,682
[grunts]

1962
01:29:50,766 --> 01:29:53,018
[both grunting]

1963
01:29:58,023 --> 01:29:59,691
[exclaims]

1964
01:30:05,864 --> 01:30:07,282
[muffled] Oh.

1965
01:30:17,167 --> 01:30:19,336
[distorted] Oh, shit.

1966
01:30:30,681 --> 01:30:31,682
[normal] Dink.

1967
01:30:31,765 --> 01:30:35,561
- [audience cheering]
- I love this fricking game, baby!

1968
01:30:35,644 --> 01:30:38,605
[triumphant music playing]

1969
01:30:38,689 --> 01:30:41,358
Unbelievable. Hammer wins it.

1970
01:30:41,441 --> 01:30:42,818
Hammer wins it on a dink!

1971
01:30:42,901 --> 01:30:44,027
Yeah!

1972
01:30:44,111 --> 01:30:47,030
Oh! We're getting
some more courts! [laughs]

1973
01:30:47,114 --> 01:30:50,742
Yeah! Yeah!

1974
01:30:54,621 --> 01:30:57,124
Yes! I'm unstoppable!

1975
01:30:57,207 --> 01:30:59,376
[cheering]

1976
01:31:06,425 --> 01:31:10,470
- [exclaims]
- [chanting] Dusty! Dusty! Dusty! Dusty!

1977
01:31:10,554 --> 01:31:12,181
We did it! We won!

1978
01:31:12,264 --> 01:31:14,850
You did it! You did it! We won!

1979
01:31:15,559 --> 01:31:17,269
Oh, I'm so happy for you!

1980
01:31:25,360 --> 01:31:28,405
Andy! Don't be too hard
on yourself, brother.

1981
01:31:28,488 --> 01:31:29,656
Yeah, I feel totally fine.

1982
01:31:29,740 --> 01:31:32,159
This isn't a real sport.
I-I don't care about anyone here.

1983
01:31:32,242 --> 01:31:34,203
All the same. You keep your head up, kid.

1984
01:31:34,286 --> 01:31:35,370
- Again, this was stupid…
- Yeah.

1985
01:31:35,454 --> 01:31:37,122
- …I'm a professional athlete…
- Yes.

1986
01:31:37,206 --> 01:31:38,707
…and your dad paid me 15 grand to be here.

1987
01:31:38,790 --> 01:31:41,877
Gladiator to gladiator, it was an honor!

1988
01:31:47,925 --> 01:31:50,594
- Yes!
- [laughs] I can't believe it.

1989
01:31:50,677 --> 01:31:52,137
Neither can I.

1990
01:31:52,221 --> 01:31:55,390
I mean, there was some luck involved
and a little cheating, but we got him.

1991
01:31:55,474 --> 01:31:57,392
Dusty, that was incredible.

1992
01:31:57,476 --> 01:31:58,477
Well, thanks to you.

1993
01:31:58,560 --> 01:31:59,853
- Mmm.
- Yeah,

1994
01:31:59,937 --> 01:32:03,774
I guess I finally realized that, you know,
I don't always have to swing so hard.

1995
01:32:03,857 --> 01:32:08,278
Yeah. It took you a really, really
long time to get that, but you did get it.

1996
01:32:08,946 --> 01:32:11,532
- I got a win.
- You got a win.

1997
01:32:11,615 --> 01:32:12,616
[chuckles]

1998
01:32:13,450 --> 01:32:16,119
Dusty, you may wanna check in on your dad.

1999
01:32:16,620 --> 01:32:18,956
Yeah, he ran back towards his office
looking pretty upset.

2000
01:32:19,039 --> 01:32:20,040
[Gene] Not good.

2001
01:32:22,000 --> 01:32:24,002
[gentle music playing]

2002
01:32:27,589 --> 01:32:28,674
Ah, shit.

2003
01:32:30,133 --> 01:32:31,134
[sniffles, cries]

2004
01:32:31,218 --> 01:32:32,678
Look, Dad, I-I'm sorry.

2005
01:32:32,761 --> 01:32:34,888
I know how much this place means to you.

2006
01:32:34,972 --> 01:32:37,474
I just… I-I didn't mean to hurt ya.

2007
01:32:38,058 --> 01:32:39,059
[sighs]

2008
01:32:41,562 --> 01:32:42,771
[sighs]

2009
01:32:42,855 --> 01:32:46,024
My boy beat Andy Roddick.
[breathes shakily]

2010
01:32:46,692 --> 01:32:48,777
Yeah, but it wasn't tennis.
It was pickleball. It's diff--

2011
01:32:48,861 --> 01:32:50,320
Doesn't matter what the game was,

2012
01:32:50,404 --> 01:32:53,615
or that I'd personally invited him
here to crush you.

2013
01:32:54,533 --> 01:32:59,788
What matters is
that my boy beat Andy Roddick.

2014
01:33:00,706 --> 01:33:03,000
I am so damn proud of you, Son.

2015
01:33:03,083 --> 01:33:04,793
- You are? [laughs]
- Oh, yes!

2016
01:33:04,877 --> 01:33:08,255
- I've waited a long time for this, Dad.
- [laughing]

2017
01:33:09,256 --> 01:33:12,676
[chuckling] It's embarrassing
how much this means to me.

2018
01:33:13,594 --> 01:33:16,638
- We always find a way, huh?
- Yeah. We finally got him.

2019
01:33:16,722 --> 01:33:20,893
- We got him! Yes! [laughs]
- We got him.

2020
01:33:21,935 --> 01:33:23,770
This is the most fun
we've ever had together!

2021
01:33:23,854 --> 01:33:25,105
- Yes!
- [laughs]

2022
01:33:25,189 --> 01:33:27,191
["Time O' Ya Life" playing]

2023
01:33:38,619 --> 01:33:39,828
[Dusty] We did it. [sighs]

2024
01:33:39,912 --> 01:33:41,330
Everything looks perfect.

2025
01:33:41,413 --> 01:33:45,292
Thank you, Mr. President
of Pickleball Operations.

2026
01:33:45,375 --> 01:33:49,880
Can you believe it, Mr. Vice President
of Pickleball Operations?

2027
01:33:49,963 --> 01:33:51,590
- Me?
- Mm-hmm.

2028
01:33:51,673 --> 01:33:52,966
That's an official title?

2029
01:33:53,050 --> 01:33:54,885
Yeah, I mean, official between you and me.

2030
01:33:54,968 --> 01:33:56,845
- And I get a pay rise?
- No, same money.

2031
01:33:56,929 --> 01:33:58,597
I cordially accept.

2032
01:33:59,097 --> 01:34:00,349
[chuckles] Wonderful.

2033
01:34:01,391 --> 01:34:04,061
Hey, I got you something
just as my way of saying,

2034
01:34:04,144 --> 01:34:07,397
"Thank ya and I see ya and I accept ya."

2035
01:34:08,065 --> 01:34:10,567
[chuckles] You're my best friend.

2036
01:34:10,651 --> 01:34:11,652
Thanks, Dusty.

2037
01:34:11,735 --> 01:34:13,904
Thanks, Peej. I gotta go schmooze.

2038
01:34:22,579 --> 01:34:24,581
My sweet, sweet Ally.

2039
01:34:25,082 --> 01:34:28,085
You've been off my radar,
but now you're back.

2040
01:34:28,168 --> 01:34:32,297
Boop. Boop. Boop. Boop.

2041
01:34:32,381 --> 01:34:33,215
[kisses]

2042
01:34:33,298 --> 01:34:34,383
I hope they're happy.

2043
01:34:35,884 --> 01:34:36,885
[Gene groans]

2044
01:34:38,387 --> 01:34:42,224
- [Chuck] Kaboom! [laughs]
- [Dusty] Oh! Nice shot, Dad!

2045
01:34:42,307 --> 01:34:44,309
We pickled them, Son. Eleven, zip.

2046
01:34:44,393 --> 01:34:46,061
- Can you believe it?
- I can't believe it.

2047
01:34:46,144 --> 01:34:49,147
Chuck, I didn't think
you could take the joy out of this

2048
01:34:49,231 --> 01:34:50,649
and you did. Respect.

2049
01:34:50,732 --> 01:34:52,109
You got pickled, Piggy.

2050
01:34:52,192 --> 01:34:56,029
Stop calling me Piggy!
My name is Skip Pigliani.

2051
01:34:56,113 --> 01:34:57,865
Okay, I'm sorry, Skip.

2052
01:34:57,948 --> 01:34:59,491
- Thank you, Chuck.
- You're welcome, Piggy.

2053
01:35:00,784 --> 01:35:02,536
Hey. You having fun?

2054
01:35:03,370 --> 01:35:06,665
I still prefer tennis, but this is,
you know, totally fine.

2055
01:35:07,165 --> 01:35:10,252
It's fun. Some of the players
are a little, uh, intense.

2056
01:35:10,335 --> 01:35:13,672
Hey, darlings, can we cut the chittychat
and get back to pickling? Thank you.

2057
01:35:14,715 --> 01:35:16,383
[grunting]

2058
01:35:17,843 --> 01:35:19,469
[groans]

2059
01:35:19,553 --> 01:35:20,971
Ladies, how's it going?

2060
01:35:21,054 --> 01:35:23,974
Would you hurry your ass up?
You're getting ready to lose.

2061
01:35:24,057 --> 01:35:25,267
Yeah, you little slut!

2062
01:35:25,350 --> 01:35:28,061
[laughs] Yes, Judy! That's the fire.

2063
01:35:28,145 --> 01:35:29,438
That is the fire.

2064
01:35:29,521 --> 01:35:33,775
Can you believe we drew Gail and Judy
in the first round? What are the odds?

2065
01:35:33,859 --> 01:35:36,486
I mean, they're high. I made the bracket.

2066
01:35:36,570 --> 01:35:39,740
- Oh. Oh, right. Aw.
- I wanted to play with friends.

2067
01:35:39,823 --> 01:35:42,284
But I also wanted a guaranteed win
and we're gonna crush 'em.

2068
01:35:42,367 --> 01:35:45,120
- Yes, let's obliterate them.
- Let's get 'em.

2069
01:35:45,204 --> 01:35:46,330
[Candace] Let's go.

2070
01:35:50,167 --> 01:35:51,668
You ready for this, Hammer?

2071
01:35:53,712 --> 01:35:58,133
- The Hammer's dead. I'm just Dusty.
- [music ends]

2072
01:35:58,800 --> 01:36:01,136
Or maybe you could be called The Dink.

2073
01:36:01,220 --> 01:36:03,472
No, I'm not gonna be called The Dink.

2074
01:36:03,555 --> 01:36:05,224
Oh, I like that for you.

2075
01:36:05,307 --> 01:36:07,601
No, it is not me.
That's not gonna be my nickname.

2076
01:36:07,684 --> 01:36:09,895
Dinky Dinky Doo, that's you!

2077
01:36:09,978 --> 01:36:11,104
You're The Dink now.

2078
01:36:11,188 --> 01:36:12,648
No, no, no. I'm not gonna be The Dink.

2079
01:36:12,731 --> 01:36:17,319
Looks like Dusty's earned himself a new
nickname. Let's see if this one sticks.

2080
01:36:17,402 --> 01:36:19,488
Uh-uh. No way, guys. I'm not gonna be the…

2081
01:36:21,490 --> 01:36:23,492
["History in the Making" playing]

2082
01:37:58,086 --> 01:38:00,088
["Cowgirl" playing]

2083
01:40:54,763 --> 01:40:56,765
[gentle music playing]